page.title: 05BUTTERFLIES AND MOTHS
page.content: In this area of open wheat fields, meadows and woodland,there are over fifty varieties of butterflies.In particular,there are such butterflies as the{Meadow Brown,}the{Gate Keeper,} the{Ringlet,}the{Tortoiseshell,}the {Red Admiral}and the{Painted Lady. Bradley Wood is privately-owned,and is very old and undisturbed.Therefore many species of moths and butterflies breed there _ amongst the moths there are the{Privet Hawk}moth,the{Eyed Hawk moth,the{Convolvulus Hawk}moth,the{ {Poplar Hawk}moth and the{Lime Hawk} moth.However the keeper brings some of the pupae into the house to hatch, after which he releases them back into the woods. Mediterranean species have been seen in these woods and it would appear that this happens when we get warm, south-westerly winds.
